**Key points about the template:**

- All colors are authored as `Colordx` objects — chainable for `.darken()`, `.lighten()`, `.saturate()` in UI helpers
- `createThemeDefinition()` walks **only `input.colors`** and converts every `Colordx` instance to its hex string via `node.toHex()`. `meta` is preserved verbatim, never touched by the walker. `Colordx` is treated as a leaf — `isWalkable()` early-outs on `instanceof Colordx`.
- Strings and any other primitives pass through unchanged
- Feedback and git are defined inline in the theme file (no separate `create-feedback-*.ts`)
- Accents reference palette colors directly (structural sharing of Colordx is safe — Colordx is immutable)
- `meta` key includes "next" to distinguish the PoC from the original in the monitor grid
- The full Colordx → hex pipeline runs through every helper (palette, ui, syntax) in Phase 1 — no half-migrated branches. `createThemeDefinition()` is the single conversion boundary for the whole theme.

### Phase 2: Migrate legacy themes to `ThemeDefinitionNext`

After Phase 1 verifies end-to-end, all 33 legacy themes move to the new shape and the legacy `ThemeDefinition` type is retired.

#### 2.1 Convert each legacy theme to `ThemeDefinitionNext`

For every theme outside the PoC:

- Replace `oklch()` calls with `colordx("oklch(...)")`
- Define raw primaries/palette/feedback/git/accents (Colordx)
- Build ui via `createUiNext` (creating dark / per-collection variants as needed — see Phase 3 table)
- Build syntax via `createSyntaxNext` (ditto)
- Wrap in `{ meta, colors: { ... } }` and pass to `createThemeDefinition()`
- Delete the now-unused per-collection `create-feedback-*.ts` (feedback inlined in each theme file)

#### 2.2 Drop the css-vars shim and legacy `ThemeDefinition`

Once every theme satisfies `ThemeDefinitionNext`:

- `themeMap`: change `Record<ThemeKey, ThemeDefinition | ThemeDefinitionNext>` → `Record<ThemeKey, ThemeDefinitionNext>`. Rename `ThemeDefinitionNext` → `ThemeDefinition` (the legacy one is now gone). Same for `ThemeUiColorsNext` → `ThemeUiColors`.
- Delete the legacy `ThemeDefinition`, `ThemeUiColors`, `ThemeUiBackgroundColors`, `ThemeUiForegroundColors` interfaces.
- Delete the legacy-flat alias emission from `themeToCssVars` (the shim in 1.2). The function simplifies to `flatten(theme.colors)`.
- Delete `getColors()` accessor — `theme.colors` is the only path now.
- Settle final names for the `Raw*` family (`ThemeAuthoringPrimaryColors` / `ThemeSourcePrimaryColors` / etc. — see Open Questions).

